of practical application

00:01:01.460 --> 00:01:05.250
of neural plasticity,
which simply means

00:01:05.250 --> 00:01:08.390
the ability of the brain
to change and rewire itself

00:01:08.390 --> 00:01:09.470
over one's lifetime.

00:01:09.470 --> 00:01:11.210
It's fantastic.

00:01:11.210 --> 00:01:14.980
The genesis of the program
lies in Barbara's own journey

00:01:14.980 --> 00:01:17.850
of discovery and innovation
to overcome her learning

00:01:17.850 --> 00:01:22.459
disabilities, a description
of which appears in her book

00:01:22.459 --> 00:01:23.250
that you guys have.

00:01:23.250 --> 00:01:25.060
So thank you for
bringing those today.

00:01:25.060 --> 00:01:27.750
And there will be a
signing afterwards.

00:01:27.750 --> 00:01:29.840
And the name of the book
is titled "The Woman

00:01:29.840 --> 00:01:32.420
Who Changed Her Brain."

00:01:32.420 --> 00:01:34.519
Many reviewers have
written about her book.

00:01:34.519 --> 00:01:36.060
To share one of the
quotes-- I really

00:01:36.060 --> 00:01:39.080
like this one-- "It will open
